---
title: Balsamic Fig Chicken with Sweet Potatoes and Mixed Greens
description: We're big fans of pan sauces because they're a simple way to add extra flavor to dishes. And you seem to be fans of them too: the fig jam and balsamic vinegar-based sauce here was such a hit with our happy cooks last time that we’re adding this recipe to the HelloFresh Hall of Fame. It’s a sweet and savory condiment that you'll want to drizzle over everything—especially the juicy chicken breasts that take center stage.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/balsamic-fig-chicken-8c98838a.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/balsamic-fig-chicken-0f9b28e2.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/balsamic-fig-chicken-59b1b46930a03b2b4e6d2ca2
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 540 kcal
  fat: 21 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 54 g
  sugar: 17 g
  protein: 40 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 480 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Cut @sweet potatoes{2} into ½-inch cubes. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until tender and crisped, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}. Strip enough and chop enough @rosemary{¼%oz} leaves from stems to give you 1 tsp. Halve @lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Pat @chicken breasts{12%oz} dry with a #paper towel{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook in pan until no longer pink in center, ~{5-7%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and set aside to rest.

Lower heat under pan to medium. Add shallot, chopped rosemary, and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}. Cook, tossing, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp} and half the @fig jam{½%oz} (use the rest as you like). Simmer until syrupy, about ~{1%minute}. Stir in ½ cup @water{½%cup} and @chicken stock concentrate{1}. Let reduce until saucy, about ~{3%minutes}. Remove from heat. Stir in @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss @mixed greens{2%oz} with a squeeze of lemon and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a medium #bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Thinly slice chicken, then divide between #plates{} along with sweet potatoes. Drizzle chicken with sauce. Serve with salad on the side.

> This fig jam and balsamic vinegar-based sauce is a sweet and savory condiment that you'll want to drizzle over everything—especially the juicy chicken breasts that take center stage.

